On behalf of all of the Shotbow staff team, I wish you a very happy new year. While 2017 had its ups and downs, we are pleased to say that we have a lot in store for 2018! We are all very excited to present our awesome projects to you – some of which have been in the works for weeks, months, and even [I]years[/I]. Here's a small teaser, as well: we're working to bring two new games to Shotbow this year - one that you're expecting and one that you're not!

In celebration of 2018, use XP code [B]2018[/B] for a nice surprise! :) On that note, please enjoy our first New Moon of 2018.

[CENTER][IMG]https://i.imgur.com/FXrKQ6A.png[/IMG][/CENTER]
 
[COLOR=#e64a19][SIZE=5][B]Christmas Event[/B][/SIZE][/COLOR]
This December, we hosted [URL='https://shotbow.net/forum/threads/the-christmas-update-dentrils-new-moon-december-2017.381058/']the Christmas event for 2017[/URL], which was super fun! Some of the things we had include: a brand new winter hub, winter-themed game maps throughout all of our games, MineZ events like the head hunt and traveling snowman, the breathtaking [URL='https://shotbow.net/forum/threads/smash-the-christmas-update.381049/']SMASH update[/URL], [URL='https://shotbow.net/forum/threads/christmas-cosmetics.381694/']brand new Christmas cosmetics[/URL] (including our first balloons), and so much more! We hope you enjoyed the Christmas event – please let us know in a comment something that you loved about it and something that you'd like to see next year!

[COLOR=#e64a19][SIZE=5][B]Minecraft 1.13 Poll[/B][/SIZE][/COLOR]
Last week, we posted a poll asking about [I]your[/I] opinion on [URL='https://shotbow.net/forum/threads/minecraft-1-13-poll.381901']what Shotbow should do regarding the Minecraft 1.13 update[/URL]. With a week left to vote, 1.9 and 1.13 as base versions are in a perfect tie, so we still need your feedback and opinions as to what we should do! Please be sure to comment on the thread with your reasoning as to why you voted for what you voted for!

[COLOR=#e64a19][SIZE=5][B]HCFactions Returns[/B][/SIZE][/COLOR]
After a long wait, HCFactions is finally back and better than ever on January 19th for an open beta. Their official statement can be found [URL='https://www.reddit.com/r/hcfactions/comments/7kvmnc/hcfactions_returns_january_19th_announcement/']here[/URL], and here is the trailer:
https://youtu.be/dt7WnH3G08Y

